講者資訊












2017/04/14講者: Prof. Shuhei Furukawa 講題: Structuring of metal-organic frameworks in multiscales


講者：Prof. Shuhei Furukawa
演講題目：Structuring of metal-organic frameworks in multiscales
演講時間：4/14（五）15:30~17:20
演講地點：博雅館 201
主持人：呂宗昕教授
 
Structuring of metal-organic frameworks in multiscales
 
 
Shuhei Furukawa 
Institute for Integrated Cell-Material Sciences, Kyoto University, Yoshida, Sakyo-ku, Kyoto 606-8501, Japan
E-mail: shuhei.furukawa@icems.kyoto-u.ac.jp
 
Assembling molecules into higher order structures by non-covalent interaction is key to emerge new functions and a complexity in chemistry and biology and the understanding of its mechanism is a ubiquitous interest over scientific disciplines. In this lecture, I focus on the usage of coordination bond as one of non-covalent interactions to produce assemblies of metal ions and organic molecules. In particular, I introduce a novel class of porous materials so-called metal-organic frameworks (MOFs) as examples. By controlling the assembly process, chemists are now able to control the size, shape and architecture of MOFs in multiscales, from the molecular level to micro-meter scale. I also talk about how we apply these scalable materials for cell biology and electronics.
 
關於本次講者資訊請參考附件檔案，謝謝。


